text: White Vine (Sarcostemma clausum) is a species of plant. It is also known as White Twinevine. It belongs in the subfamily Asclepiadoideae. It is native to southeastern United States, Mexico, the Caribbean, Central America and South America as far south as Paraguay. ==References== ==Other websites== *Sarcostemma clausum at Atlas of Florida Vascular Plants *Sarcostemma clausum at USDA PLANTS Database Category:Apocynaceae
title: Sarcostemma clausum
